fuzz_extract_mem: assert `dmc_unrar_filters_get_first_length(&ctx->filters) > 0`
at dmc_unrar.c:7980 inside dmc_unrar_rar50_decompress. The RAR5 LZ
path pulls the next filter from the filter queue and expects its
length to be non-zero, but a malformed archive can declare a
zero-length filter that slips through filters_empty(). 195-byte
input, surfaced on the 60-second fuzz_extract_mem smoke run taken
right after Phase 6 caps (file-count/file-size/total-size/ratio/PPMd)
landed. Awaiting fix: needs a runtime rejection of zero-length
filters, analogous to the earlier zero-width Huffman table fix, before
the fixture can be wired into fuzz_regressions[].
